article:
'BPS' can stand for:

;In science, mathematics and technology *Base pairs, a measure of length of DNA
using the number of nucleotide pairs *Basis points, equal to one one-hundredth
of a percentage point *Battered person syndrome, a physical and psychological
condition found in victims of abuse *Berkeley printing system *Bisphenol S, an
organic chemical compound *Bits per second, the speed of transfer or playback of
a digital file *Bladder pain syndrome, a disorder characterised by pain
associated with urination *Bogomol'nyi-Prasad-Sommerfield bound, a mathematical
concept in field and string theory *Bronchopulmonary sequestration, a disorder
where a section of lung tissue has a decreased blood supply *IBM Basic
Programming Support, BPS/360

;Organizations *Badan Pusat Statistik, a government institute of Indonesia
that conducts statistical surveys *Banque Populaire Suisse, a Swiss bank
(German: {{lang|de|Schweizerische Volksbank}}) *Bass Pro Shops, a retailer of
hunting, fishing, camping and related outdoor recreation merchandise *Bermuda
Police Service, the law enforcement agency of Bermuda *Biophysical Society,
an organization consisting of over 8,000 biophysics researchers *Black P.
Stones, a street gang in Chicago, United States *Blue Planet Software
(formerly Bullet-Proof Software), a video game developer *Board of Pharmacy
Specialties, a post-licensure certification agency for specialized
pharmacists *British Pharmacological Society, the professional association
for pharmacologists in the United Kingdom *British Psychological Society, the
representative body for psychologists and psychology in the United Kingdom
*British Pteridological Society, the focal point for fern enthusiasts
throughout the United Kingdom *Buddhist Publication Society, a charity aiming
to spread the teachings of Buddha

;Schools *Bangkok Patana School, a British international school in Bang Na,
Thailand *Belilios Public School, a government secondary school in Hong Kong
*Blackfriars Priory School, a private Catholic school in Adelaide, Australia
*Boston Public Schools, a school district in Boston, Massachusetts, United
States *British Parachute Schools, a parachuting drop zone in Nottinghamshire,
England *Buffalo Public Schools, a school district in Buffalo, New York, United
States *Berkeley Preparatory School, a school in Tampa, Florida from grades Pre-
K through 12.

;Other uses *BabyPinkStar, an electro glam punk band in Sheffield, England
*Battle Programmer Shirase, an anime TV series *Balls Per Second, the rate of
fire of a paintball gun *Baltic Pipeline System, a oil transport system in
Western Europe *Battersea Power Station, a disused power station in London,
England *British Parliamentary Style, a common form of academic debate *'BPS',
IATA code for Porto Seguro Airport, Brazil
